This paper is about data augmentation for image classification tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques, such as GoogLeNet, to improve classification accuracy, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a new data augmentation technique, which involves generating new samples from existing ones, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of limited training data, which is a common problem in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions medical imaging tasks, which is a sub-field of multimedia (cs.MM).
